", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "use case inspired by @satra \r\n\r\nusing datalad for backing up into google drive or S3 or ... which enforces limitation not only on size but also on inodes. \r\n\r\nRIA stores with ORA archives sounds like a good way to establish such backups but they would hit the max size limit (5TB for S3 and google drive).  Would be nice if RIA store automagically established multiple archives whenever getting close to reach the size limit (may be even with some backfill of prior ones if an additional file fits).\r\n\r\nI wonder if feasible at all to keep as an open issue", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5654/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5654/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}